[http://www.flickr.com/photos/51979177@N02] Good finds! I think the NSW Government interest for those photos was primarily the new-style wharves.  I am always a lot wary of Series 4481 names and dates - they give &quot;c. 1/01/1901&quot;

This photo, fairly reliably dated from the Tivoli advert at September 1902 by yours truly 40 months ago when Trove was a new toy, shows the new wharves under construction at left, the Paragon at right without Christies Umbrellas sign. ....

